          This new Salvadorian restaurant opened up next to my house called El Mirador, and it's friggin' phenomenal.  Best steak and cheese tacos I've ever had.  Anyway, I was looking at their business card today, and it's all in Spanish.  Now I can speak a little Spanish, but I wanted a second opinion, so I typed what the card had written on to it into the AltaVista Babel Fish translator.  This is what it said:<br /><br />SPANISH: "Con el sabor de la abuela, mama, y la nuestra!" =<br />ENGLISH: "With the flavor of the grandmother, it sucks,  and ours!"<br /><br />I soon realized that there was a slight typo... it should have been "de mama" instead of just "mama."  I corrected this error and it said this:<br /><br />SPANISH: "Con el sabor de la abuela, de mama, y la nuestra!" =<br />ENGLISH: "With the flavor of the grandmother, the breast, and ours!"<br /><br />Hmm... while I'm sure I know what they were getting at, I'm still a little weirded out by the whole "it sucks, grandmother, breast" thing.  On the other hand, it kind of just really makes me want a taco.<br /><br />
